---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Results — Formic"
  description="Real outcomes from real production floors. 20% OpEx reduction, 24/7 support, $0 CapEx, 12-week deployments."
  ogTitle="Results — Formic"
  ogDescription="Measurable impact from Formic Full Service Automation."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/results" slot="head" />

  <style is:global slot="head">
.res-statsrow{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(240,245,241,.1);max-width:1280px;margin:36px auto 0}
.res-statsrow .stcell{background:var(--dgrey);padding:48px 28px;text-align:center}
.res-statsrow .stnum{font-family:var(--sans);font-size:64px;font-weight:500;color:var(--white);line-height:1;display:block;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
.res-statsrow .stlbl{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55)}
@media(max-width:900px){.res-statsrow{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
  </style>

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>Results
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Results</div>
    <h1>Real results from <em>real production floors</em>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">20% OpEx reduction. Zero capital. Two-week deployment. The numbers Formic customers see, again and again, and the four reasons mid-market CPG operators automate with Formic.</p>
    <div class="res-statsrow">
      <div class="stcell"><span class="stnum" data-count-to="20" data-suffix="%">0%</span><span class="stlbl">OpEx Reduction</span></div>
      <div class="stcell"><span class="stnum" data-count-to="24" data-suffix="/7">0/7</span><span class="stlbl">Bilingual support and monitoring</span></div>
      <div class="stcell"><span class="stnum" data-count-to="0" data-prefix="$">$0</span><span class="stlbl">CapEx Required</span></div>
      <div class="stcell"><span class="stnum" data-count-to="2" data-suffix=" wks">0 wks</span><span class="stlbl">Avg. Deployment</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Overcoming Labor Shortage</div>
      <h2>Automate the <em>hardest-to-fill</em> positions.</h2>
      <p>Mid-market CPG operators are losing 25-40% of their workforce annually on the worst-positioned tasks: palletizing, case packing, and end-of-line work. Formic automates those roles, reducing turnover exposure without eliminating the experienced operators you actually want to keep.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Targets the highest-turnover positions on the floor</li>
        <li>Frees experienced operators for higher-value work</li>
        <li>Reduces dependence on temporary and seasonal labor</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/stories" class="larr">See customer stories →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Operator-Hairnet-Working.jpg" alt="Operator in hairnet and safety glasses hands-on with a Formic case-packing cell — the skilled role Formic preserves while automating the high-turnover tasks around it" loading="lazy"/></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Wyandot-Palletizing.jpg" alt="Formic palletizing cell — robot taking on the high-strain stacking task" loading="lazy"/></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Eliminating Ergonomic Injury</div>
      <h2>Cut injury rates. <em>Improve retention.</em></h2>
      <p>Formic customers have documented reductions in workers' comp claims after removing operators from repetitive lifting, twisting, and overhead-reach tasks — with improvements in retention on adjacent roles. The ROI shows up in workers' comp before it shows up in throughput.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Targets repetitive lifting, twisting, and overhead-reach tasks</li>
        <li>Documented reductions in workers' comp claims at customer sites</li>
        <li>Improves operator retention on adjacent, less-strenuous roles</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/stories" class="larr">See customer stories →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Productivity Gains</div>
      <h2>Throughput you can <em>plan around</em>.</h2>
      <p>Consistent cycle times, faster changeovers, and real-time OEE data for continuous optimization. Formic customers report measurable reductions in line variance and scrap after deployment and planning cycles that no longer depend on shift-to-shift operator consistency.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Sustained cycle-time consistency vs. operator-bound variance</li>
        <li>Faster changeovers between SKUs and formats</li>
        <li>Real-time data feeds into your MES and ERP</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/stories" class="larr">See customer stories →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Formic-Pallet-Wrapper.jpg" alt="Formic automated pallet wrapper finishing a stack of cases — consistent throughput, hands-off changeovers" loading="lazy"/></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Cameron-Cobot-Palletizing.jpg" alt="Formic cobot palletizing fleet at Cameron's — fixed monthly price, no CapEx" loading="lazy"/></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">04 — Cost Savings</div>
      <h2>One fixed monthly price. <em>Zero capital risk.</em></h2>
      <p>An OpEx model that scales with growth and with usage. Formic customers consistently report 20%+ OpEx reduction on automated lines compared to their pre-Formic baseline with no depreciation surprises, no obsolete equipment, and no integrator handoffs.</p>
      <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:300;color:rgba(240,245,241,.62);margin:14px 0 0"><a href="https://land.formic.co/automations-roi-vs-tco-know-the-full-story-before-you-invest" style="color:var(--orange);font-weight:500;text-decoration:none">Read: ROI vs TCO — the full story before you invest →</a></p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Predictable monthly cost, written into the contract</li>
        <li>No CapEx required — frees capital for higher-leverage uses</li>
        <li>Equipment swaps and upgrades included in the agreement</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/stories" class="larr">See customer stories →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:96px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="db-tag">Industries we serve</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(32px,4vw,56px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1.05;color:var(--black);margin:8px 0 14px">Real results, <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">your industry</em>.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:16px;font-weight:300;color:var(--dgrey);max-width:720px;margin:0 0 32px;line-height:1.6">Snack food, candy, dairy and cheese, nuts and dried fruit, commercial baking — see how operators in your industry put Formic to work.</p>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey)">
      <a href="/results/snack-food" style="background:var(--white);text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;transition:background .2s" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--lgrey)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--white)'">
        <div style="aspect-ratio:16/10;overflow:hidden;background:var(--black)"><img src="/Wyandot-Palletizing.jpg" alt="Wyandot Snacks Formic palletizing cell" loading="lazy" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block"/></div>
        <div style="padding:22px 22px 26px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange)">Industry</div>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:20px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black);line-height:1.2;margin:0">Snack food</h3>
          <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.55;color:var(--mgrey);margin:0">Wyandot Snacks scales shipments without hiring up.</p>
          <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange);margin-top:6px">See industry →</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/results/candy" style="background:var(--white);text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;transition:background .2s" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--lgrey)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--white)'">
        <div style="aspect-ratio:16/10;overflow:hidden;background:var(--black)"><img src="/stories/taffy-town/1763757449-taffytown-0219.jpg" alt="Taffy Town production floor" loading="lazy" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block"/></div>
        <div style="padding:22px 22px 26px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange)">Industry</div>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:20px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black);line-height:1.2;margin:0">Candy</h3>
          <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.55;color:var(--mgrey);margin:0">Taffy Town: 5.5M lbs of taffy palletized with Formic.</p>
          <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange);margin-top:6px">See industry →</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/results/dairy-and-cheese" style="background:var(--white);text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;transition:background .2s" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--lgrey)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--white)'">
        <div style="aspect-ratio:16/10;overflow:hidden;background:var(--black)"><img src="/stories/rumiano-cheese/1745598936-rumiano-1.jpg" alt="Rumiano Cheese palletizing cell" loading="lazy" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block"/></div>
        <div style="padding:22px 22px 26px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange)">Industry</div>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:20px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black);line-height:1.2;margin:0">Dairy &amp; cheese</h3>
          <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.55;color:var(--mgrey);margin:0">Rumiano, Masters Gallery, and Sunrise Family Farms.</p>
          <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange);margin-top:6px">See industry →</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/results/nuts-and-dried-fruit" style="background:var(--white);text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;transition:background .2s" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--lgrey)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--white)'">
        <div style="aspect-ratio:16/10;overflow:hidden;background:var(--black)"><img src="/stories/georgia-nut/1642517481-screen-shot-2022-01-14-at-2-49-19-pm.png" alt="Georgia Nut palletizing cell" loading="lazy" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block"/></div>
        <div style="padding:22px 22px 26px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange)">Industry</div>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:20px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black);line-height:1.2;margin:0">Nuts &amp; dried fruit</h3>
          <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.55;color:var(--mgrey);margin:0">Georgia Nut and Mariani Packing drive throughput.</p>
          <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange);margin-top:6px">See industry →</span>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/results/commercial-baking" style="background:var(--white);text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;transition:background .2s" onmouseover="this.style.background='var(--lgrey)'" onmouseout="this.style.background='var(--white)'">
        <div style="aspect-ratio:16/10;overflow:hidden;background:var(--black)"><img src="/stories/uncle-crumbles/1749483799-screenshot-2025-06-09-at-8-43-04-am.png" alt="Uncle Crumbles bakery automation" loading="lazy" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block"/></div>
        <div style="padding:22px 22px 26px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px">
          <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange)">Industry</div>
          <h3 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:20px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black);line-height:1.2;margin:0">Commercial baking</h3>
          <p style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:14px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.55;color:var(--mgrey);margin:0">Uncle Crumbles, Mi Rancho, and the ABA partnership.</p>
          <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange);margin-top:6px">See industry →</span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Numbers your CFO<br><em>will actually like</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="/contact/get-a-quote" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/" class="btn-ctawh">Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</section>

  <script is:inline slot="scripts">
(function(){
  const els=document.querySelectorAll('.stnum[data-count-to]');
  if(!els.length)return;
  const ease=t=>1-Math.pow(1-t,3);
  function run(el){
    const target=parseFloat(el.dataset.countTo)||0;
    const prefix=el.dataset.prefix||'';
    const suffix=el.dataset.suffix||'';
    const dur=1400,start=performance.now();
    function step(now){
      const t=Math.min(1,(now-start)/dur);
      const v=Math.round(target*ease(t));
      el.textContent=prefix+v+suffix;
      if(t<1)requestAnimationFrame(step);
    }
    requestAnimationFrame(step);
  }
  const obs=new IntersectionObserver(entries=>{
    entries.forEach(e=>{if(e.isIntersecting){run(e.target);obs.unobserve(e.target);}});
  },{threshold:.4});
  els.forEach(el=>obs.observe(el));
})();
  </script>
</Layout>
